      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2023-05-17</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-03-01T19:34:37Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Upholding a Secure Postal System Act or the USPS Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill requires the Government Accountability Office to investigate nationwide patterns and instances of theft of mail and U.S. Postal Service (USPS) property and report to Congress.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Any such report must include a description of any measures that the USPS has in place to address, and recommendations on how the USPS and Congress can combat, such theft.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
